; Regression test for issue #834: --pedantic doesn't work if specified in Ledger file (BZ#834)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/834
;
; When --pedantic is placed in the journal file itself (rather than on the command line),
; it should enforce strict checking of accounts, commodities and tags. However, the bug
; is that --pedantic in the file is silently ignored -- undeclared accounts cause no error.

--pedantic

commodity $
    format $1,000.00

account Expenses:Food
account Assets:Cash

2024/01/01 Declared accounts
    Expenses:Food       $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/02 Undeclared account
    Expenses:Unknown    $5.00
    Assets:Cash

; BUG: With --pedantic active, this should fail because Expenses:Unknown is not declared.
; Currently ledger ignores the in-file --pedantic and succeeds (exit 0) instead of
; erroring on the unknown account. The correct behavior (matching command-line --pedantic)
; would be to exit 1 with an "Unknown account" error.

test bal
             $-15.00  Assets:Cash
              $15.00  Expenses
              $10.00    Food
               $5.00    Unknown
--------------------
                   0
end test
